# Pearls content pipeline (year-scoped)

Canonical operator guide: `WORK-FLOW.md`.

When the user asks to parse / prepare / enrich a year (e.g. «парсим 2019»):

1. `npm run content:year -- <year>`
2. Review `data/parsed/<year>/`
3. Always run `npm run metadata:ai -- --year=<year> --write` for new year data
4. `npm run generate:downloads -- --year=<year>`
5. Commit `data/parsed`, then ship downloads + code (`sync:downloads` + `deploy:code`, or documented deploy scripts)

Rules:

- Always pass `--year` or `--file`. Never run `prepare:docx`, `parse:word`, or `metadata:ai` against the whole archive by default.
- `parse:word` does not call OpenAI. `metadata:ai` is a separate step; for a new year it is expected, not optional.
- Inside `metadata:ai`, documents with a usable title are skipped (token saver). Do not pass `--force` unless the user asks.
- Do not put `SOURCE_PERALS` on production. Prod needs reviewed `data/parsed/` (git) and prebuilt `web/public/downloads/` (rsync) only.
- Do not hand-edit `data/parsed/` JSON.
